<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 03 at 3:13PM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Buchanan and
southwestern McDowell Counties through 345 PM EDT...
At 311 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Grundy, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and hail up to half an inch
in diameter.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Grundy, Gary, War, Bradshaw, Stacy, Vansant, Coalwood and Jolo.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
